						               													<description>Straightforward tactical game of the battle involving AJAX, EXETER, ACHILLIES and THE GRAF SPEE off the River Plate early in WW2.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;An independent small-press publication with heavy cardstock components and poor diecutting - but diecut units nevertheless!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is one small strategic map in the game, and several tactical maps (one for each ship involved). Each player has gunnery and torpedo markers for his ships.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The tactical maps are kept hidden from the opponent and moves are plotted with units on these maps, then translated into movement on the strategic map.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Victory conditions are simple enough with the win going to the side sinking all the enemy. If the turn limit is reached then damaged and sunk British ships factor into a victory calculation.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Damage charts include hit location and various special effects (speed loss, gunnery loss, jammed rudders etc.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
